PING

ping google.com - checks whether your system is connected to Google server or not
 to exit ping use "ctrl + c"
ping -c 4 gloogle.com - it prints 4 packets they stop

ip/ifconfig -it shows ip address,mac address (modern linux uses "ip") 

netstat - it shows network statistics ( like connection,ports)
netstat -a - shows all connections
netstat -tuln - it shows listening ports
       t - tcp ,u - udp , l - listening , n - numeric addresses

ss - used to faster replacement for netstat
ss -a - shows all connections
ss -tuln - shows listening ports

curl - used to send http request and access apis
curl -o https://example.com/hello.txt - to download file 
curl -X POST https://example.com/hello - send post request

wget 

wget url - download files from the internet
wget -b url -download in background
wget -c url resumes itterupted downloads

scp 
scp used to transer files between systems using ssh

scp a.txt user@192.168.1.10:/home/user/ - used to copy file to remote server

ssh 

ssh used to access remote login
ssh guru@192.168.1.10 - then enter psw then u will get remote access.
ssh guru@192.168.1.10 "ls -l" - run commands on remote server


EVN

evn  shows alll environment variables in the system

echo $home - we usednecho to check specific variable

export name=guru - used to create or modify environment variable
echo $name - to check variable

uname

uname is used to display system and kernal information
uname -a - show all system information
uname -r - shows kernal version
uname -m - machine architecture
uname -s - os name

hostname -it shpws server name in the network
sudo hostname newserver - used to change host name temporary
whoami - used to show current logged -in user
who - used to show all users currently login into the system
uptime - shows how long the system has been running snice last time the system was started
date - shows date and time
date "+%Y-%m-%d" - custom date format(shows date only)
date "+%H-%M-%s" - shows time only

history - shows list of commands previously executed in the terminal
!4 - run previous command using history number
!! - run last command again
history -c - clear history
history > commands.txt - save history to file

alias 
alias name='guruprasad' - it used to create short name for a long command now u can use name where u use guruprasad
alias - used to view all alias
unalias alias_name - removes an alias command
unalias -a - used to remove all alias
which python - shows the path of a command executable
whereis python-used to show location of binary,source code

clear used to clears the terminal screen 
ctrl + L =it is a shortcut
exit - it closes the current terminal 


> - redirects the output of a command to a file (if file already exist it overwrites the content
ls > hello.txt - it saves the output of "ls" into files.txt

*
>> - used to add output to the end of the file instead of replacing it
echo "first line" > file.txt - 
*

< - it sends input fron a file to a command 
command < hello.txt
wc -l < hello.txt - it counts lines from the file
| - this is pipe used to send output of ond command as a input of another command
ls | wc -l  - means ls is list files and wc -l is counts them

2> - it redirects error messages to a file
ls wrongfile 2> hello.txt - instead of displaying the error it shows hello.txt

& -runs a command in background 
sleep 100 & - it runs background

cal - used to display calender in terminal
cal 2 2026 - it shows 2 nd moth calender of 2026 in terminal
cal 2026 - it shows all 12 months on that year
cal -3 - it shows 3 months calender
cal -m - to start with monday (default it contains sunday)
cal -v - it shows vertical calender
